386→                        <div id="content">Let $c&#62;0$ and let $f_c(n)$ be the maximal $m$ such that every graph $G$ with $n$ vertices and at least $cn^2$ edges, where each edge is contained in at least one triangle, must contain a book of size $m$, that is, an edge shared by at least $m$ different triangles. <br><br>Estimate $f_c(n)$. In particular, is it true that $f_c(n)&#62;n^{\epsilon}$ for some $\epsilon&#62;0$? Or $f_c(n)\gg \log n$?</div>
